Reviewed `src/blog/people/drafts/Tyler1.md` and appended a `FRESH EYES REVIEW (2026-05-19)` block at the bottom.

Two biggest issues flagged:

1. **The 5'5" jacked bodybuilder identity is entirely absent.** The "tiny screaming gym bro" silhouette is one of the first things any casual viewer registers, and skipping it (plus his real name, Tyler Steinkamp) will read to fresh eyes like the piece hasn't actually watched him.
2. **The Adderall setup never pays off, and Missouri/billboard/mom-brings-dinner repeats four times.** The chemically-managed-since-age-six line is the most interesting thread in the draft and gets dropped, while the small-town anchor lands so often it becomes the writer's tic instead of an insight.

Smaller but worth noting: no current critic (Phreak from 2017 is the only one), and the "no friends / sovereign" reading smooths over the real contradiction that his audience is, by any honest measure, the tribe.
